	 <bioghist encodinganalog="545"> 
		<p>Irvin Goodman (1897-1958) was a Portland, Oregon native and was
		  admitted to the Oregon Bar in 1924. He became a well-known and successful defense attorney, working on such cases as those of Nicolai Gregorovich Redin, and Wayne and Sherry Fong. He died from a heart ailment in 1958.</p> 
	 </bioghist> 
	 <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a"> 
		<p>Collection includes: Speeches, papers, reminiscences and notes on the
		  judicial system, civil rights, espionage, discrimination and class conflict;
		  Correspondence, 1950-1959, regarding speaking engagements, writing projects,
		  etc.; Newspaper clippings and scrapbooks regarding his cases, including the
		  Nicolai Redin spy case and many murder cases.</p> 
	 </scopecontent> 
<arrangement encodinganalog="351"> 
		<p>The collection is arranged in the following series: 
		  <list> 
			 <item>Series A: Comments and speechs</item> 
			 <item>Series B: Manuscripts</item> 
			 <item>Series C: Other loose materials</item> 
			 <item>Series D: Scrapbooks</item> 
		  </list></p> 
	 </arrangement> 	 
